{"word":"νεόω","slug":"νεόω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>νεόω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:νέος'><el>νέος</el></a>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>only used in aor1\n<p/><i>to renovate, renew</i>, <el>νέωσον</el> <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>:—<a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <el>τάφους ἐνεώσατο</el> <i>had</i> them <i>renewed</i>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/>"}]}